The Chronicle Bongani Ndlovu, Online Reporter African Sun Limited, through one of its subsidiaries – Holiday Inn today handed over a freshly renovated ward to Mpilo Central Hospital in Bulawayo. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-687528" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/3-2-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/3-2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/3-2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The ward is situated on the 3rd floor of Mpilo Central Hospital. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-687527" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/WhatsApp-Image-2023-03-08-at-10.18.22-680x380.jpeg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/WhatsApp-Image-2023-03-08-at-10.18.22.jpeg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/WhatsApp-Image-2023-03-08-at-10.18.22-360x200.jpeg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> In attendance are Holiday Inn General Manager, Mrs Amanda Mathema,  Mpilo Central Hospital Chief Medical Officer Dr Narcious Dzvanga, and senior staff from Holiday Inn and the hospital. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-687531" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/1-3-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/1-3.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/1-3-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The 34-bed ward has had linen replaced,  repainted, tiled, and ablution facilities were redone, with the addition of new bathtubs. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-687534" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/2-2-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="htt